Habitat & Distribution:— Inocybe vaurasii is a species with a preference for continental forests of Fagaceae , especially Fagus sylvatica in Europe, but also found associated with Quercus robur in Sweden ; it does not seem to show a marked edaphic preference for soil ph, although most of the studied collections come from calcareous soils or at least more nutrient rich soils. Based on the collections studied and data obtained from GenBank, its distribution area extends throughout humid continental Europe ( Germany , Denmark , France , Italy , Spain and Sweden ), but it is also known to exist in northern Iran , as shown by GB reference FR852271 , which corresponds to the Fagaceae forests of the Hyrcanian Forests (
Bahram et al. 2012
). Some citations refer to I. xanthomelas or I. cf. asterospora , due to their morphological similarity (see Table 1 ).

